cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular languages and finite automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the efficiency of determining whether a language is accepted by a finite automaton. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper considers the complexity of determining whether a language is accepted by a finite automaton. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial properties of regular languages. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the properties of bordered and unbordered words, which can be related to geometric concepts such as convex hulls.
